  <TITLE>dos</TITLE>

  <TYPE>Scilab Function</TYPE>

  <DATE>October 2005</DATE>

  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="dos">Execute a DOS command and return result (for
  windows 2k and more)</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>

  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>stat=dos(command-name)</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>

    <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>[stat,output]=dos(command-name)</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>

  <PARAM>
    <PARAM_INDENT>
      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>command-name</PARAM_NAME>

        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: A character string containing dos command</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>

      <PARAM_ITEM>
        <PARAM_NAME>stat</PARAM_NAME>

        <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
          <SP>: An boolean</SP>
        </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
      </PARAM_ITEM>
    </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>

  <DESCRIPTION>
    <P>dos command calls upon the shell to execute the given command for
    Windows systems. status = dos('command') returns %t if it is OK.</P>

    <P> [status,result] = dos('command') in addition to completion status,
    returns the result of the command to the result variable.</P>

    <P>dos is used by "unix, unix_w, ..." under windows 2k and more.</P>
  </DESCRIPTION>

  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
[stat,output]=dos('dir')
[stat,output]=dos('date')
 
  ]]></EXAMPLE>

